(v_mod2, 'If a deed to two people does not specify the type of co-ownership, what is typically presumed?', '["Joint tenancy", "Community property", "Tenancy in common", "Tenancy by the entirety"]', 2, 1),
(v_mod2, 'What is a key benefit of having a written TIC agreement?', '["It eliminates all taxes on the property", "It prevents any co-owner from ever selling", "It establishes clear rules for expenses, use, and dispute resolution", "It guarantees the property will appreciate in value"]', 2, 2),
(v_mod2, 'In a TIC arrangement, can one owner sell their share without consent from the others?', '["Never under any circumstances", "Yes, generally they can, though TIC agreements may add restrictions", "Only if a court approves the sale", "Only if all owners agree in writing"]', 1, 3),
(v_mod2, 'What is a partition action?', '["A request to divide the property into separate legal parcels", "A legal proceeding to force the division or sale of co-owned property", "A method of creating a new tenancy in common", "An insurance claim for property damage"]', 1, 4),
